SIMPLE: overact
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overact
<hw>O`ver*act"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
act or perform to excess; to exaggerate in acting; <as>as, he
<ex>overacted</ex> his part</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To act upon, or influence, unduly.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The hope of inheritance <qex>overacts</qex> them.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overact</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Overact
<hw>O`ver*act"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To act more than
is necessary; to go to excess in action.</def> <rj><au>B.
Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overaction</ent>⟦br⟧
